OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA largely dry day with sunny
OL,6,Fspells in the south and east. Cloudier
OL,7,Facross Perthshire and Stirling with
OL,8,Fpatchy rain. Remaining warm,
OL,9,Fespecially in the east.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA cloudy start to the evening
OL,12,Fin the west but a bright end to the
OL,13,Fday elsewhere. Remaining dry overnight
OL,14,Fwith lengthening clear spells. A mild
OL,15,Fnight.
OL,16,
OL,17,CMonday:FA largely dry day with plenty
OL,18,Fof sunshine and feeling warm. Cloudier
OL,19,Fwith a little rain early in the
OL,20,Fevening across northern Perthshire.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
